# Threatseeker Report - Cron Schedule Template
#
# SETUP INSTRUCTIONS:
# 1. Edit this file and replace YOUR_USERNAME and YOUR_GITHUB_USERNAME
# 2. Run: crontab -e
# 3. Paste the line below (without the # comment)
# 4. Save and exit
#
# VERIFY:
#   crontab -l | grep threatseeker
#
# LOGS:
#   tail -f ~/.claude/logs/threatseeker-report-cron.log
#
# ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES:
#   CTI_GIT_REPO     - Required for auto-push (set inline or in shell profile)
#   CTI_OUTPUT_DIR   - Output directory (default: /tmp/threatseeker-report)
#   CTI_AUTO_PUSH    - Enable auto-push (default: true)
#   CTI_HISTORY_DAYS - Days for deduplication (default: 7)

# Run daily at 8:00 AM
# UPDATE: Replace YOUR_USERNAME and YOUR_GITHUB_USERNAME below

0 8 * * * CTI_GIT_REPO="git@github.com:YOUR_GITHUB_USERNAME/threat-intel-reports.git" /home/YOUR_USERNAME/.claude/scripts/threatseeker-report-runner.sh >> /home/YOUR_USERNAME/.claude/logs/threatseeker-report-cron.log 2>&1

# Alternative: If you set CTI_GIT_REPO in your shell profile (~/.bashrc or ~/.profile)
# 0 8 * * * /home/YOUR_USERNAME/.claude/scripts/threatseeker-report-runner.sh >> /home/YOUR_USERNAME/.claude/logs/threatseeker-report-cron.log 2>&1

# Alternative times:
# 0 6 * * *   - 6:00 AM daily
# 0 9 * * 1-5 - 9:00 AM weekdays only
# 0 */6 * * * - Every 6 hours
